                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d322">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500A4B/576: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-12-05T12:00:00+09:00"
                            >December 5, 1934—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received December 4—11:30
                        p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>269. Reference my telegram No. 267, December 3, 1 p.m., first paragraph, last
                    sentence. My Italian colleague<note n="52" xml:id="d322fn52">Giacinto
                        Auriti.</note> informs me that <pb facs="0508" n="408" xml:id="pg_408"/>
                    acting under instructions from Rome he informed the Japanese Government
                    yesterday afternoon very briefly that Italy did not care to join in denunciation
                    of the treaty but that it was ready to participate in any conference to be held
                    under the terms of article 23 after denunciation by Japan.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
